The State Capture Inquiry continues its focus on the public broadcaster. JOHANNESBURG - The Commission will hear South African Broadcasting Cooperation (SABC) related testimony from Dr Ben Ngubane, Leonard Lekgetho and Anton van Vuuren. Last week veteran journalist Joe Thloloe and Fhatuwani Lastborn Mutuvhi gave testimony. READ: Ex-SABC CEO describes Gupta mansion visit Thloloe was dealing with evidence relating to alleged interference at the public broadcaster. He led the editorial interference report into the SABC He told the commission that there was “no evidence of a direct line between decisions at ANC headquarters, Luthuli House, and decision in the newsroom, but the spectre of the ANC hovered over the newsroom.”